name: transroad-lrs2005
notes: LRS2005 is a Linear Referencing System layer that includes interstate, U.S., state (VT), and other transportation routes logged by the Vermont Agency of Transportation. These routes are represented in the ETE and TWN route subclass. ETE stands for End-to-End route system, meaning that routes increment from start to finish without resetting at town boundaries. TWN stands for Town-Based route system, meaning that routes increment from start to finish within each town, resetting at town boundaries. Linework and attributes were extracted from TransRoad_RDS (7/2005 version of RDSMALL - 2005 HMS update).
